The paper deals with visual robot navigation, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The approach presented in the paper involves using a visual Simultaneous Localization And Mapping (SLAM) system, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the challenges of dealing with uncertainties in real-time robotics applications, which is a problem that can be addressed using artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The creation of a topological map involves clustering and graph theory, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper presents experiments on a mobile robotic platform, which falls under systems and control (cs.SY).
